social-personal development and ability to adapt, even when the infant had not had more
maternal contact. Additionally, a 50% parenting time presumption has myriad collateral benefits:
including lower overall divorce rates,22 higher rates of child support compliance,23 greater overall
parental health,24 reducing litigation, thereby reducing the strain on court resources and the
stress on children.25
